{"DIADELPHIA":[{"def":"A Linnæan class of plants whose stamens are united into two bodies or bundles by their filaments.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to the class Diadelphia; having the stamens united into two bodies by their filaments (said of a plant or flower); grouped into two bundles or sets by coalescence of the filaments (said of stamens).","pos":""}],"DIADEM":[{"def":"An arch rising from the rim of a crown (rarely also of a coronet), and uniting with others over its center.","pos":""}],"DIADROM":[{"def":"A complete course or vibration; time of vibration, as of a pendulum.","pos":""},{"def":"The separation or resolution of one syllable into two; -- the opposite of synæresis.","pos":""}]}